// Q1: IMAGE_TAG = "${env.GIT_COMMIT.take(7)}"
//     GIT_COMMIT is Jenkins' built-in variable for the triggering commit's full SHA;
//     .take(7) trims it to 7 characters (e.g., 'a1b9f3c').

// Q2: The 'Test' stage runs before 'Build Image'.
//     If tests fail, the pipeline aborts before spending time building and pushing
//     an image that would never be deployed — fail fast, waste nothing.

// Q3: 111122223333.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/my-app:a1b9f3c
//     (GIT_COMMIT.take(7) on 'a1b9f3cdef012' yields 'a1b9f3c')
//     Format: <account-id>.dkr.ecr.<region>.amazonaws.com/<repo>:<tag>

